          <p class='first-para'>
            This has been a helpful discussion. I am not sure to what extent it was wholly related to the amendments&#x2014;to a considerable extent, I think&#x2014;but we need to be clear about the matter. As the noble Baroness said, this perhaps deals with the last unreformed piece of Beveridge. While there may not be any votes in it, it is a matter that should be borne in mind when we go on, as the Bill does, extending the anomalies in the way suggested.</p><p>
            I wonder where best we might raise the issues of retrospection and so on.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
