        <q>Page 91, line 40, leave out "A minister of the Crown" and insert "The Secretary of State</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07317'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_318' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: This may be a matter that the Minister referred to in his opening remarks. Generally speaking, we would expect the Secretary of State rather than a Minister of the Crown to make amendments to various enactments relating to pensions, including pensions generally and Church legislation&#x2014;a matter on which the right reverend Prelate the Bishop of Chelmsford may have something to say. It seems more appropriate for that to be done by the Secretary of State rather than a mere Minister. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0661P0-07318'>
