      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07470'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_471' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 193 [<span class="italic">Minor and consequential amendments and repeals</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07471'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_472' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Baroness Crawley</span> moved Amendment No. 92H:
        <q>Page 95, line 28, at end insert "and revocations</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07472'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_473' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Baroness said: In moving Amendment No. 92H, I shall speak also to Amendments Nos. 102 to 104. Amendment No. 92H makes a technical change to Clause 193(1) by adding "revocations" after "repeals". This change is necessary as the new material added in relation to child support and social security arrangements for Northern Ireland amends Northern Ireland Orders in Council. In strict drafting terms the provisions of Orders in Council, as a species of subordinate legislation, are revoked and not repealed.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07473'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_474' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The other amendments to Schedule 22 are consequential to the inclusion in Schedule 17 of new material for the provision of social security and child
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_518gc' title='Col. 518GC &mdash; HL Deb 25 May 2004 vol 661 c518GC' name='column_518gc' href='#column_518gc' rel='bookmark'>518GC</a>
        support in Northern Ireland. Similar repeals are already contained in Schedule 22 which are consequential on the amendments to social security and child support legislation in Great Britain. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07474'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_475' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07475'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_476' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 193, as amended, agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07476'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_477' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 20 [<span class="italic">Minor and consequential amendments: general</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07477'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_478' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Baroness Crawley</span> moved Amendment No. 92J:
        <q>Page 234, line 11, at end insert&#x2014;</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07478'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_479' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="italic">"<a href="/acts/interpretation-act-1978">Interpretation Act 1978</a> (c. 30)</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07479'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_480' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        At the appropriate place in Schedule 1 (words and expressions defined) insert&#x2014;
        <q>"Civil partnership" means a civil partnership which exists under or by virtue of the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a> (and any reference to a civil partner is to be read accordingly).&#x2014;</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-07480'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_481' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Baroness said: This is a simple amendment which inserts a new entry into Schedule 1 to the <a href="/acts/interpretation-act-1978">Interpretation Act 1978</a> to define the terms "civil partnership" and "civil partner". Under Sections 5 and 23 of the <a href="/acts/interpretation-act-1889">Interpretation Act</a>, if an expression listed in Schedule 1 is used in any Act or subordinate legislation, it is to be interpreted in accordance with that schedule unless the Act or subordinate legislation in question shows a contrary intention. The amendment means that references in other legislation to "civil partnership" or "civil partner" will be interpreted by reference to the <a href="/bills/civil-partnership-bill">Civil Partnership Bill</a>. This will ensure that courts, tribunals and others who use and interpret the legislation are given a clear signpost to this Bill. It will also save those drafting legislation from any uncertainty about whether to include specific definitions. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0661P0-07481'>
        <a name='S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_482'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-terence-higgins' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_482' title='Link to this speech by Mr Terence Higgins' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-terence-higgins" title="Mr Terence Higgins">Lord Higgins</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Does the expression "civil partnership" appear anywhere else?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0661P0-07482'>
        <a name='S5LV0661P0_20040525_GCR_483'>  </a>
